T1	Context 729 816	the applicant's grievances fall to be examined solely under Article 6 § 2 of the Convention
T2	Context 1749 1841	the termination of the applicant's employment was directly related to the events leading to the criminal proceedings
T3	Context 1841 1969	the labour court examined the criminal file and based its reasoning to a great extent on its contents
T4	Option 1969 2059	a strong link between the criminal and labour proceedings existed
T5	Option 2072 2141	Article 6 § 2 is applicable in the context of the labour proceedings at issue
T6	Option 2155 2247	this complaint is not manifestly ill-founded within the meaning of Article 35 § 3 of the Convention
T7	Option 2286 2310	declared admissible
T8	Context 2340 2471	the nature of the labour court's task was to assess whether the termination of the applicant's employment had been justified
T9	Context 2483 2601	the Bakırköy Labour Court, as a civil court not bound by the findings or result of the criminal proceedings, was at liberty to determine the dispute from a labour law perspective
T10	Option 2614 2743	reach a different conclusion from the criminal courts by establishing independently the facts of the case with regard to the applicant's conduct
T11	Context 2761 2912	exoneration from criminal responsibility does not, as such, preclude the establishment of civil or other forms of liability arising out of the same facts
T12	Option 2961 3088	the national courts in the subsequent proceedings need to stay within the bounds of a civil forum and refrain from suggesting criminal characterization of the applicant's conduct
T13	Option 3089 3196	Any statement or reasoning by a civil court calling into question the applicant's established innocence would be incompatible with the requirements of Article 6 § 2
T14	Context 3218 3390	the Bakırköy Labour Court was empowered to make a fresh assessment of the facts, it based its reasoning to a large extent on the criminal file, and concluded that the applicant had indeed committed the offence of incitement
